import React, { useState } from "react"; import { Anomaly } from "../types/insights"; import { AlertTriangle, TrendingUp, GitBranch, Zap, ChevronDown, ChevronRight, Link2, ArrowRight, Container, Server, Database, Shield, Layers, Timer, Gauge, Activity, Target, Network, } from "lucide-react"; interface AnomaliesTableProps { anomalies: Anomaly[]; } const AnomaliesTable: React.FC = ({ anomalies }) => { const [expandedRows, setExpandedRows] = useState>(new Set()); const [filterSeverity, setFilterSeverity] = useState("all"); const [filterType, setFilterType] = useState("all"); const toggleRow = (id: string) => { const newExpanded = new Set(expandedRows); if (newExpanded.has(id)) { newExpanded.delete(id); } else { newExpanded.add(id); } setExpandedRows(newExpanded); }; const getSeverityColor = (severity: string) => { switch (severity) { case "critical": return "bg-red-100 text-red-800 border-red-200"; case "high": return "bg-orange-100 text-orange-800 border-orange-200"; case "medium": return "bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 border-yellow-200"; case "low": return "bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 border-blue-200"; default: return "bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 border-gray-200"; } }; const getTypeIcon = (type: string) => { switch (type) { case "burst_correlation": return ; case "lead_lag": return ; case "pmi_correlation": return ; case "change_attribution": return ; default: return ; } }; const getTypeColor = (type: string) => { switch (type) { case "burst_correlation": return "text-blue-600 bg-blue-50"; case "lead_lag": return "text-green-600 bg-green-50"; case "pmi_correlation": return "text-purple-600 bg-purple-50"; case "change_attribution": return "text-orange-600 bg-orange-50"; default: return "text-gray-600 bg-gray-50"; } }; const getTypeLabel = (type: string) => { switch (type) { case "burst_correlation": return "Burst Correlation"; case "lead_lag": return "Lead-Lag Relationship"; case "pmi_correlation": return "PMI Co-occurrence"; case "change_attribution": return "Change Attribution"; default: return "Unknown"; } }; const formatAnomalyMessage = (message: string) => { // Clean up the message for better readability return message .replace(/Strong co-occurrence:/g, "") .replace(/Change attribution:/g, "") .replace(/Lead-lag relationship:/g, "") .replace(/Burst correlation:/g, "") .replace(/\(PMI \d+\.\d+, support \d+\)/g, "") .replace(/\(correlation \d+\.\d+\)/g, "") .replace(/after \d+\.\d+min/g, "") .trim(); }; const filteredAnomalies = anomalies.filter((anomaly) => { const severityMatch = filterSeverity === "all" || anomaly.severity === filterSeverity; const typeMatch = filterType === "all" || anomaly.type === filterType; return severityMatch && typeMatch; }); const renderDetails = (anomaly: Anomaly) => { const details = anomaly.details; switch (anomaly.type) { case "burst_correlation": return (
Correlation
{(details.correlation * 100)?.toFixed(1)}%
Statistical correlation
Aligned Bursts
{details.aligned_bursts} / {details.total_buckets}
Simultaneous spikes
{details.correlation_basis && (

Burst Analysis

Pattern
{details.correlation_basis.burst_pattern?.replace( "_", " " )}
Trigger
{details.correlation_basis.correlation_trigger?.replace( "_", " " )}
Intensity
{details.correlation_basis.burst_intensity?.toFixed(1)}σ
)}
); case "lead_lag": return (
Lag: {details.lag_seconds}s ( {details.direction})
Correlation:{" "} {details.correlation?.toFixed(3)}
Granger Score:{" "} {details.granger_score?.toFixed(3)}
Confidence:{" "} {details.confidence?.toFixed(3)}
); case "pmi_correlation": return (
PMI Score
{details.pmi_score?.toFixed(2)}
Pointwise Mutual Information
Support
{details.support}
Co-occurrence count
Confidence
{(details.confidence * 100)?.toFixed(1)}%
Statistical confidence
Total Buckets
{details.total_buckets}
Time windows analyzed
{details.token_a && details.token_b && (

Token Relationship

{details.token_a}
{details.token_b}
)} {details.correlation_basis && (

Correlation Analysis

Trigger Type
{details.correlation_basis.correlation_trigger?.replace( "_", " " )}
Pattern
{details.correlation_basis.temporal_pattern?.replace( "_", " " )}
Occurrences
{details.correlation_basis.co_occurrence_count}
Density
{details.correlation_basis.co_occurrence_density_per_hour?.toFixed( 1 )} /hr
Time Span
{details.correlation_basis.total_time_span_hours?.toFixed( 1 )} h
{details.correlation_basis.affected_namespaces?.length > 0 && (
Affected Namespaces
{details.correlation_basis.affected_namespaces.map( (ns: string, idx: number) => ( {ns} ) )}
)}
)}
); case "change_attribution": return (
Lag Time
{details.lag_minutes?.toFixed(1)}min
Delay between cause and effect
Correlation
{(details.correlation_coefficient * 100)?.toFixed(1)}%
Strength of relationship
Changes
{details.change_count}
Triggering events
Effects
{details.effect_count}
Resulting events
); default: return ( 
            {JSON.stringify(details, null, 2)}
); } }; return (
{/* Filters */}
{/* Professional Card Layout */}
{filteredAnomalies.map((anomaly) => (
{/* Card Header */}
{/* Type Badge */}
{getTypeIcon(anomaly.type)} {getTypeLabel(anomaly.type)}
{anomaly.severity.toUpperCase()}
{/* Message */}

{formatAnomalyMessage(anomaly.message)}

{/* Timestamp */}
{new Date(anomaly.timestamp).toLocaleString()}
{/* Expand Button */}
{/* Expanded Details */} {expandedRows.has(anomaly.id) && (
{renderDetails(anomaly)}
)}
))} {filteredAnomalies.length === 0 && (

No anomalies found

No anomalies match the current filters.

)}
); }; export default AnomaliesTable;
